Germany first in Europe introduces ‘uncertain sex’ when registering children
Germany will become the first country in Europe to be allowed to indicate “uncertain” when registering children born with hermaphrodite, instead of male or female.
The parents of the child will have the right to leave the column "floor" in the birth certificate for time unfilled.
Instead of "F" (female sex) or "M" (male sex), parents can temporarily write "X" (uncertain).
