The Treaty on Open Skies was signed in 1992, with 34 states participating.
Observation flights are made over the territories of Russia, the USA, Canada, and European countries.
The main objectives of the Treaty are to promote transparency, to promote the monitoring of the implementation of arms control agreements, to expand opportunities to prevent crises and to resolve crisis situations within the OSCE and other international organizations.
