Everything except the IT industry.
And yet, the coverage and technical development of U.S. espionage agencies, which became known by Snowden’s revelations, were shocked by some companies that previously thought that China was the biggest risk of surveillance.
A major shift is taking place in cloud technologies, where European company executives have become better aware that data stored in the U.S. are in the same jurisdiction and are therefore potentially vulnerable.
