George Kerevan: the gap with Europe gives the Scots a choice
Another day, another horror story about independence.
This time we are warned that an independent Scotland will have to join the pan-European zone of free movement as a condition for EU membership.
There is a turn of stories about passport control in Berwick and the border with barbed wire along the Hadrian shaft.
True, the Strathclyde newspaper pointed to the possible economic benefits of freer movements across the rest of Europe, although – what is predictable – it did not appear in the headlines.
