Now the "Smolenskaya" is almost over.
The flower stall disappeared, the stand for newspapers was dismantled, and the asphalt was replaced by paving stones before the entrance.
Here is the entire transport hub.
Transport and interchange units are flat and capital, - explained in the press service of the Moscow Department of transport.
There are no capital TPUs yet.
And flat ones involve the construction of parking lots, the withdrawal of retail facilities that interfere with the movement of passengers, the creation of small architectural forms and improvement.
Actually, flat TPUs are not even engaged in transport workers, but professional landscapers from the Department of capital repairs of the city of Moscow.
The transport hub is not necessarily a complex design, ”explains Mikhail Blinkin, director of the Institute of Transport Economics and Transport Policy of the Higher School of Economics.
Sometimes a roof over your head and a scoreboard are enough to notify about the time of arrival of the transport.
Here, for example, at the metro "Yasenevo" recently opened a quite full flat interchange unit.
Let without canopies, but with intercepting parking lots and scoreboards indicating when the bus arrives.
But in the pursuit of the number, officials write down everything that gets into the TPU.
Back in 2011, the mayor’s office planned to build 151 knots for everything, 59 of them with capital construction.
Now the plans until 2020 are as many as 255 TPUs.
One and a half of them promise to pass this year.
