Report by the number of objects, but the quality of the transfer on each of them often deteriorates.
The criteria, according to the expert, should be two: firstly, a decrease in the transfer time, and secondly, convenience.
First of all, the ability to change the type of transport without going out in the rain.
In Moscow, when arranging TPU, sometimes comes exactly the opposite.
A vivid example of the VDNH metro.
Previously, suburban buses from the Yaroslavsk highway came to the square before the main entrance to the All-Union Technical University.
Now their stops were transferred to the opposite side of Yaroslavka to the Cosmonauts Street.
Further from the metro, much farther from the monorail, but closer to residential buildings.
It is a gift that the residents did not want the bus station under the windows and complained to all possible authorities.
With the capital TPU in Moscow somehow did not immediately ask.
The first of them began to build five years ago near the metro "Planernaya".
The project was designed to be exemplary.
And really turned out a sample of how the interchange hub, given to investors, turns into a banal shopping center.
No, there are platforms for buses, a canopy, so as not to go from the subway in the rain, and three floors of car parks.
However, Khimki trolleybuses No. 202 and No. 203 in the Moscow TPU did not give places fundamentally.
They were pushed away from the subway as strangers.
There is more room for trade.
Only the clothes of 32 stores, and in general there is almost everything - from pet goods to the car dealership.
Well, in fact, what if from the passengers of the bus will need to buy a new car on the road?
When we build a capital TPU, for some reason, there is always a shopping center.
Recently, the situation has reached its logical conclusion, when part of the parking lot decided to give to the market.
Now on the third floor of TPU "Planernaya" among the parking spaces marked on the floor is a brisk trade.
Vegetables, spices, Chinese jeans, non-Russian speech and guards, visually pleasing to our photographer.
The transfer hub finally turned into a bazaar.
The fact is that earlier the metro "Planernaya" was a market, but it was demolished.
And in the prefecture, merchants were spared and allowed to intercept the interchange hub.
It’s still empty because of the high prices.
The funny thing is that the market was demolished in order to build in its place. New flat TPU.
That's the castling.
At the Kaluga metro, the distance of the approach from the metro lobby to the bus was 50 meters, - says Alexander Morozov.
After the construction of the shopping center, allegedly TPU, the distance increased to 170 meters.
To get on the bus, you need to go through the entire shopping center.
After 22 hours, when it is closed, you have to bypass it in the open air.
However, the designs on the "Planner" and "Kaluga" will soon seem to be flowers.
In mid-September, the city planning and land commission of the city hall approved planning decisions for the first eight capital TPUs.
Four of them will be 25-storey, not counting two or three underground tiers.
The main monster will grow near the metro station "Tushino", it will be 418.7 thousand square meters. Meters of area.
Representatives of the Directorate of Railway Stations, responsible for the construction of TPU near the metro, have already told reporters: in future high-rise buildings will be located shops, hotels and apartments.
At the same time, officials assure that multi-tier parking will take from a third to half of the area.
Take the example of "people's" garages.
For example, a garage for 258 cars, which was recently built on International Street, has an area of 8015 sq.m. meters.
So, for parking for 2.6 thousand cars, "Petrovsko-Dzumovskaya" will need about 80 thousand "squares".
This is less than a third of the machine that they are going to build there.
Let one or two floors go to all sorts of platforms for buses.
There are at least 150 thousand square meters. Meters of Commercial Real Estate.
And this, for a moment, almost two GUMS.
If the capital TPU at the stations and railway stations are built, then the other sites will be mastered by metro.
They also promised that there would be many “functional facilities”, including hotels, offices and even gyms.
By the way, the Department of Property of the city of Moscow recently told reporters that they are developing a draft resolution, according to which investors will be able to apply for a site for TPU directly.
Without any competitions.
Because, they say, transport issues for the city are a priority.
The ideal TPU is, for example, the Harvard station in Boston or Spaignin in Toronto, Alexander Morozov is sure.
There, trolleybuses and trams descend underground to the metro level and the distance from the subway car to the tram is only 50 meters without going out.
There's no extra trade around.
But Moscow officials are being put to extreme.
Either we will not build anything, or we will not kill 25 floors with offices and apartments.
